########## Rhea script ##########

## Set functions ###

# Calculate the species richness in a sample
Species.richness <- function(x)
{
  # Count only the OTUs that are present >0.5 normalized counts (normalization produces real values for counts)
  count=sum(x[x>1]^0)
  return(count)
}

# Calculate the Shannon diversity index
Shannon.entropy <- function(x)
{
  total=sum(x)
  se=-sum(x[x>0]/total*log(x[x>0]/total))
  return(se)
}

# Calculate the effective number of species for Shannon
Shannon.effective <- function(x)
{
  total=sum(x)
  se=round(exp(-sum(x[x>0]/total*log(x[x>0]/total))),digits =2)
  return(se)
}


#remake otu table with Abundance2
otu_table<- dcast(Turnstone.Family, Family~Library, value.var = "Abundance2") #tip over the table
otu_table$Family<-NULL #remove all coloumns wiht non-numeric information.. only numbers.
otu_table[is.na(otu_table)] <- 0 ## replace NA with 0

# Clean table from empty lines
otu_table <- otu_table[!apply(is.na(otu_table) | otu_table=="",1,all),]

# Order and transpose OTU-table
my_otu_table <- otu_table[,order(names(otu_table))] 
my_otu_table <-data.frame(t(my_otu_table))

# Apply diversity functions to table## 
otus_div_stats<-data.frame(my_otu_table[,0]) 
otus_div_stats$Richness<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Species.richness)
otus_div_stats$Shannon<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Shannon.entropy)
otus_div_stats$Shannon.effective<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Shannon.effective)

otus_div_stats

Turnstone.Family<-aggregate(exp_count ~ Library + Family +Age + Reads, data=avian, FUN=sum)
#Calculate "abundance" which is the proportion of total reads
Turnstone.Family$Abundance<-(Turnstone.Family$exp_count/Turnstone.Family$Reads)*100
Turnstone.Family$Abundance2<-Turnstone.Family$Abundance*100000


### Ordination with Phyloseq, which is EXTREMELY ANNOYING! #####

#justphyloseqthings

map2$Age <- c("1o", "2o", "3+", "1o", "3+")
map2$Time <- c("arrival", "arrival", "arrival", "departure", "departure")
map2$exp_count<-NULL
map2 <- sample_data(map2)##make meta data into phyloseq format

5.3.1 Virus Cluster level Alpha Diversity

### aggregate by viral family ###
NonVertCluster<-aggregate(exp_count ~ Library + NonVertCluster +Age + Reads, data=Invert, FUN=sum)
#Calculate "abundance" which is the proportion of total reads
NonVertCluster$Abundance<-(NonVertCluster$exp_count/NonVertCluster$Reads)*100
NonVertCluster$Abundance2<-NonVertCluster$Abundance*100000

#do this to extend the "Paired" palette beyond 8. 
colourCount = length(unique(NonVertCluster$NonVertCluster))
getPalette = colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(9, "Paired"))
#bars
ggplot(NonVertCluster, aes(x=Library, y=Abundance, fill=NonVertCluster)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity") + scale_fill_manual(values = getPalette(colourCount))+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))+ 
  facet_grid(.~Age, scales="free", space ="free") + 
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8, 1))

#export 7.34 x5.05

### Relative Abundance from Normalization script#####
otu_table<- dcast(NonVertCluster, NonVertCluster~Library, value.var = "Abundance") #tip over the table
#remove taxonomy info from otu_table
taxonomy <- as.vector(otu_table$NonVertCluster)
otu_table$NonVertCluster <- NULL
otu_table[is.na(otu_table)] <- 0 ## replace NA with 0

#Calculate relative abundance from otu_table
rel_otu_table <- t(100 * t(otu_table) / colSums(otu_table))
rel_otu_table<-as.data.frame(rel_otu_table)
rel_otu_table_tax <- cbind(taxonomy, rel_otu_table)

##Recast back to long form
RelAb<-melt(rel_otu_table_tax, id.vars="taxonomy")
RelAbSort<-RelAb[order(RelAb$taxonomy),] ## sort by Taxonomy

#names(colors) <- levels(RelAbSort$taxonomy)
#colScale <- scale_fill_manual(name = "Fam",values = colors)

### add back in age metadata using an ifelse statement!

RelAbSort$Age<-NA
RelAbSort$Age<-ifelse(RelAbSort$variable=="Bird.18", "1o", RelAbSort$Age)
RelAbSort$Age<-ifelse(RelAbSort$variable=="Bird.19", "2o", RelAbSort$Age)
RelAbSort$Age<-ifelse(RelAbSort$variable=="Bird.20", "3+", RelAbSort$Age)
RelAbSort$Age<-ifelse(RelAbSort$variable=="Bird.21", "1o", RelAbSort$Age)
RelAbSort$Age<-ifelse(RelAbSort$variable=="Bird.22", "3+", RelAbSort$Age)

ggplot(RelAbSort, aes(variable, value, fill=taxonomy)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position="fill") + labs(y = "Relative Abundance") + 
  facet_grid(.~Age, scales="free", space ="free") +
  labs(x= "Library") + guides(fill=guide_legend(title="Virus Family")) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = getPalette(colourCount))

#export 7.34 x5.05


#remake otu table with Abundance2
otu_table<- dcast(NonVertCluster, NonVertCluster~Library, value.var = "Abundance2") #tip over the table
otu_table$NonVertCluster<-NULL #remove all coloumns wiht non-numeric information.. only numbers.
otu_table[is.na(otu_table)] <- 0 ## replace NA with 0

# Clean table from empty lines
otu_table <- otu_table[!apply(is.na(otu_table) | otu_table=="",1,all),]

# Order and transpose OTU-table
my_otu_table <- otu_table[,order(names(otu_table))] 
my_otu_table <-data.frame(t(my_otu_table))

# Apply diversity functions to table## 
otus_div_stats<-data.frame(my_otu_table[,0]) 
otus_div_stats$Richness<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Species.richness)
otus_div_stats$Shannon<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Shannon.entropy)
otus_div_stats$Shannon.effective<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Shannon.effective)

otus_div_stats

#export 9x5.05

#remake otu table with Abundance2
otu_table<- dcast(NonVertFamily, NonVertFamily~Library, value.var = "Abundance2") #tip over the table
otu_table$NonVertFamily<-NULL #remove all coloumns wiht non-numeric information.. only numbers.
otu_table[is.na(otu_table)] <- 0 ## replace NA with 0

# Clean table from empty lines
otu_table <- otu_table[!apply(is.na(otu_table) | otu_table=="",1,all),]

# Order and transpose OTU-table
my_otu_table <- otu_table[,order(names(otu_table))] 
my_otu_table <-data.frame(t(my_otu_table))

# Apply diversity functions to table## 
otus_div_stats<-data.frame(my_otu_table[,0]) 
otus_div_stats$Richness<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Species.richness)
otus_div_stats$Shannon<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Shannon.entropy)
otus_div_stats$Shannon.effective<-apply(my_otu_table,1,Shannon.effective)

otus_div_stats

#the row names here are the library names

df$Time <- c("arrival", "arrival", "arrival", "departure", "departure")
